post_text: ACT test info!
shared_text:
Danbury Student Services
September 3 at 1:37 PM ¬∑

EXCITING ACT NEWS!!!!!

ACT has provided an option for schools to hold a test date with only their students. Therefore, students can take the National Administration of the ACT at Danbury High School on Saturday, October 24, 2020, if they register on act.org.

***IMPORTANT*** You will need to contact Mrs. Hegsted for the Test Center Code ‚Äì you will not be able to find it on the ACT website. You will need this code when you register! (Mrs. Hegsted's contact information is below.)

The registration deadline is September 17, 2020 ‚Äì without a late fee.

Late registration starts September 18, 2020 and is open until September 25, 2020 ‚Äì with a late fee.

Email: hegstedv@danburyschools.org

Schoology: Vicki Hegsted

Phone: (419) 798-4037

The other National Administration ACT testing date at Danbury High School will be Saturday, June 12, 2021.

post_text:
An important reminder as we welcome our in-person learners back to school tomorrow:
Following our drop off and pick up assignments is more important than ever to ensure the safety of our students and staff as we return to school. Due to this, all students are REQUIRED to follow the locations and times described below.

7:15 - 7:30 Grades 5-12 Drop Off:
5-12 students arriving by car are to be dropped off at the Main (HS/Central Office) flagpole entrance.

8:15 - 8:30 Grades K-4 Drop Off:
K-4 students arriving by car are to be dropped off on the East Elementary entrance.

3:00 Grades 5-12 Pick Up:
All 5-12 students being picked up in the afternoon will also be at the Main (HS/Central Office) flagpole.

3:30 Grades K-4 Pick Up
All K-4 students being picked up in the afternoon will be behind the Elementary (Playground North Doors).

We can't wait to see all of you in person tomorrow!!

Open House 2020
Welcome to the 2020-2021 school year! We are so excited to have our Lakers and their families back (no matter which of the 3 options chosen)! In an effort to social distance our families and provide the safest environment possible we are offering our open house over the course of two evenings. We ask that our families adhere to this schedule and be prepared to enter our building, following our district safety procedures (This will also allow for our students to be exposed to and practice some of our safety protocols).
Details on our website: http://bit.ly/DLSOpenHouse2020

post_text:
PARENTS:
There is still time to share your thoughts on remote instruction with us. We've had over 100 responses, so thank you to those who have submitted, but we'd love to hear from EVERY Danbury family.
We've had this question a few times: If you have multiple children who had very different experiences, feel free to submit the survey for each child separately.
Hope you're having a great summer!
shared_text:
DOCS.GOOGLE.COM
COVID-19 Remote Learning Survey for Parents

Danbury Local Schools
June 4 at 11:54 AM ¬∑

COVID-19 Remote Learning Survey for Parents.
https://forms.gle/KTkPFffT6jKbQhT58

Danbury Parents:
As we close out the 2019-20 school year and turn our thoughts to 2020-21, we felt it was very important to gather your feedback on your experiences for the past few months. Thank you all for your patience and hard work as we transitioned into an alternative learning format due to the COVID-19 pandemic. We hope to return to school in the fall, but know that this will depend on a close monitoring of the virus over the summer and rely on guidance from state and local authorities.

In order to plan for a full return, as well as a possible blended learning models for the fall, we need your input! Please take a few moments to provide us your feedback. Delivering the best possible educational experience to our Lakers is of the greatest importance to us.

Thank you for taking the time to answer these important questions.

The fourth grade wax museum has been an annual event at Danbury and this year is no exception! Take a moment to check out our very first "virtual" wax museum. Great job 4th graders!

A few "tech notes": To get the full effect, view on a desktop, laptop or Chromebook and click the "present" button to start.

#LAKERS

post_text:
We are currently organizing a senior graduation parade with assistance from the Danbury Township Police Department and the Lakeside-Marblehead Fire Department. This driving parade will take place on Sunday, May 17th beginning at 1:00 p.m. If students would like to participate, they should be in the west school parking lot ready to go by 12:50 p.m. Students should decorate their vehicles for this drive around the peninsula, which will last approximately 20-30 minutes. The parade route is as follows:

-We will exit the west end of the school parking lot and turn right onto East Harbor Rd.

-We will turn left Quarry Rd.

-We will turn left onto East Bayshore Rd.

-After turning left on East Bayshore Rd., we will follow that road around the peninsula (East Harbor Rd.) and back into the school parking lot.

PARENTS and STUDENTS:
Service: "Giving of time and talents to better our community" is more important than ever during the challenging time we're living. Please take a moment and reflect on all of the many acts of service you see in our school community every day.
The survey to nominate Danbury community members who best represent our core value of Service is now available. Every student is encouraged to nominate someone, whether it is a fellow student, staff member or someone from our Danbury community outside of the school. Use the link below to submit your nominations:
https://forms.gle/cBZHc4xWcCLJsrJB8

Think about the people you know who model these qualities and tell us about them through the survey link.
Our honorees will be showcased virtually so keep an eye out for those in the coming weeks!

Submissions will be accepted until Thursday, May 14th

#service

Seniors: Josten‚Äôs Cap & Gown Pick-Up Information:
On Wednesday, April 29th from 9:00 a.m.-11:00 a.m. Josten‚Äôs will be distributing senior caps, gowns, announcements, & other graduation items in a drive thru format in front of the athletic lobby. Students may enter the west entrance parking lot by the football practice field and drive up to the athletic lobby entrance to get their items. Students may only pick up items that have been paid for in full. You can bring cash (sorry, no checks) on the 29th or you can go online to the Josten's website and pay by using a credit card. Once you have received your graduation items you will exit the school parking lot by the cafeteria. Students will not need to get out of their vehicle and all personnel helping to hand out your graduation items will have face masks and gloves for the protection of all parties involved.

Dear Students and Parents,
This morning we experienced intermittent outages for at least two of our commonly used learning websites: Schoology and Seesaw. Unfortunately, this is something that all of us should be braced for as the whole world dramatically increases usage of online learning and remote work. We will all do our best to remain flexible and adapt to our changing environment as we work through this situation together. Teachers and school staff know the challenges we're all facing right now and have set their expectations accordingly.
In an effort to improve our communication on this topic, we have started collecting links to the status pages of our most commonly used online resources. If you're having trouble accessing something, please check this page first to see if there is an outage for that site.
http://bit.ly/DanburyResourceStatus

post_text:
Good afternoon

I wanted to take a moment and commend our staff, students, families, and community for rallying together as we navigate these new waters. Everyone's patience and continuity has been much appreciated.

Moving forward we will continue to do our best to be proactive and communicate information as we create our next steps and strategies.

I can't reinforce enough the importance of parental monitoring of our student involvement. Students actively involved in their learning is essential during these challenging times.

Next week is spring break, please take this time and enjoy your family... we will return to our remote instruction beginning on Monday March 30th. In addition, meal pick-up will take place from 6-7 pm on Monday March 30th.

Should you have questions or concerns please don't hesitated to reach out.

Have a wonderful spring break!

Superintendent Cari Buehler
March 12 at 5:56 PM ¬∑

Good Afternoon,

As you may already be aware, Governor Mike DeWine announced an extended closure of public schools in Ohio this afternoon.

Danbury Schools will be closed beginning Tuesday March 17th for 3 weeks.

The district is awaiting further clarification from the Ohio Department of Education regarding the specific details of the school closure mandate.

Based on Governor DeWine's executive order pertaining to mass gatherings, our Cabaret performances are cancelled. Other event cancellations will be shared out.

We will communicate out additional information when it becomes available.

Thank you for your continued patience during this time.

PARENTS and STUDENTS: The survey to nominate members of our school community who best represent our Danbury core value of Excellence is now available. Every student is encouraged to nominate someone, whether it is a fellow student, staff member or someone from our Danbury community outside of the school. Use the link below to submit your nominations.

https://forms.gle/LCcjmqarxoVq3ewG9

Our definition of the Danbury core value of Excellence is:

"Demonstrating your best every day through hard work and maintaining high standards."

Think about the people you know who model these qualities and tell us about them through the survey link!

Submissions will be accepted until Wednesday, February 19th and those who are selected will be honored during a ceremony to be held on Thursday, February 27th at 10:30am in the Danbury Gym

Once again, the Danbury Science Department would like to ask for your support as we will again be holding a Science Olympics this year. The Danbury Science Olympics will be held this year on Monday evening, March 9th, 2020. All students in grades 6-8 will be participating in this event. The Science Olympics will be a competition involving a variety of problem-solving situations. We are requesting your assistance in making this 17th Annual Danbury Science Olympics a continued success.
More information and a sign-up form are available here: http://bit.ly/DanburySO
Thank You!

PARENTS and STUDENTS: The survey to nominate community members who best represent our Danbury core value of Kindness is now available. Every student is encouraged to nominate someone, whether it is a fellow student, staff member or someone from our Danbury community outside of the school. Use the link below to submit your nominations.

https://forms.gle/DLpQV8PV2rvFbPKb9

Our definition of the Danbury Core Value "Kindness" is:

"Using positive words and actions while displaying empathy to be inclusive and accepting of all."

Think about the people you know who model these qualities and tell us about them through the survey link!

Submissions will be accepted until Wednesday, January 22nd and those who are selected will be honored during a ceremony to be held on January 30th at 10:30am in the Danbury Gym

#kindness

Faith was awarded $95,000 in scholarships over four years, which included the Wittenberg University Scholar Award and the Early Ezry Award. #excellence https://t.co/oPuAEj5BqT
